    <br>
    <h2>What did I do before Neumont?</h2>
    <p>
        Before Neumont, before the pandemic, I was actually a robotics student. I desperately wanted to be a mechanical engineering student.
        I had been a football player for about a year and a half before an injury, and then I dedicated myself to being a part of our robotics team.
        During this time, I was teaching myself how to program in Java, CSS, HTML, and Python. Meanwhile, I was actively learning in school how to make
        printed circuit boards, wire electrical systems, how to machine my own parts, and how to use 3D modeling software.
    </p>
