     <h2>How did I get to where I am now?</h2>
     <p>
         Being a part of my robotics team, I got to meet a lot of people who would help me in my journey into STEM. I have met and worked with the
         Department of Defense, local refineries, and even worked with the New Orleans Pelicans. These big experiences really drove me into a STEM 
         career, but I decided on software development as opposed to mechanical engineering once college rolled around. I realized my love for computers
         was deeper than my enjoyment for building new things. (It's also so much easier to code than it is to build without connections and resources.)
     </p>
